Reference-contexts: At a more abstract level, syntagmatic proximity can be viewed as symbolizing conceptual relatedness <ref> (Langacker 1985) </ref>. Hence the frame unit at the conceptual level corresponds (prototypically) to a clause unit at the syntactic level. Gapping constructions relate not just the fillers of the roles in a single frame but also the various fillers of the same role in different frames.
